2020-09-22T08:39:46: A compound thin-plate weir that was superseded by the Ash at Mardock (38002).
Compound thin-plate weir that was reconstructed in 1976 to increase flow range. It was decommissioned in 1981 and was superseded by the Ash at Mardock (38002).
It was subject to bypassing and was inaccurate at low flows.
Solid geology of Upper Chalk extensively overlain by boulder clay, glacial sands & gravel and alluvium in the valleys. Rural catchment in character.
